    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This topic was moved here from <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"113489\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/Why.20have.20the.20cast.20operators.20disappear.3F\">#new members &gt; Why have the cast operators disappear?</a> by <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110637\">Ching-Tsun Chou</span>.</p>",
        "id": 497812269,
        "sender_full_name": "Notification Bot",
        "timestamp": 1738733569
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110637\">Ching-Tsun Chou</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/Why.20have.20the.20cast.20operators.20disappeared.3F/near/497812231\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>the cast operators disappeared from both LHS and RHS of h2, even though I explicitly spelled them out.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That's because cast operators are polymorphic and try to cast as little as possible. Here there's the option to not cast at all, so they do just that</p>",
        "id": 497835452,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1738744399
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>have h2 : (initSeg α #s : Set α) \\ {f a} = initSeg α (#s - 1)</code> or <code>have h2 : (initSeg α #s).toSet \\ {f a} = initSeg α (#s - 1)</code> will work</p>",
        "id": 497835630,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1738744463
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks!  That works.  I have to say working with the <code>Fin n</code> types is truly a pain.</p>",
